# This function calls Chicago geometric from census package and picks only 
# tracts of Cook's county which are within the limits of city of Chicago
chicago_tracts <- function() {
  chicago <- get_acs(geography = "tract", 
                     variables = "B19013_001", 
                     state = "IL", 
                     county = c("Cook"), 
                     geometry = T)
  # MEDIAN HOUSEHOLD INCOME IN THE PAST 12 MONTHS (IN 2018 INFLATION-ADJUSTED DOLLARS)
  
  chicago_tracts <- read.csv("/Users/taiebat/Desktop/Chicago-TNC-analysis/CensusTractsTIGER2010.csv")
  needed<-which(chicago$GEOID %in% chicago_tracts$GEOID10)    
  chicago <- chicago[needed,]
  return(chicago)
}
chicago <- chicago_tracts()

Daily Pick-ups in Downtown Zone and out of Downtown Zone

shared <- data %>% 
  group_by(start_date) %>% 
  summarise("in_dt_zone" = sum(is_downtown_zone_surcharge, na.rm = T),  # daily number of trips in DT Zone
            "out_dt_zone" = sum(!is_downtown_zone_surcharge, na.rm = T),  # daily number of trips NOT DT Zone
            "pct_sharedOK_in_DT_zone" = (sum(is_downtown_zone_surcharge[shared_trip_authorized], na.rm = T) / sum(is_downtown_zone_surcharge, na.rm = T)),
            # daily percent of total rides that are (authorized to be) shared in DT Zone
            "pct_sharedOK_out_DT_zone" = (sum(!is_downtown_zone_surcharge[shared_trip_authorized], na.rm = T) / sum(!is_downtown_zone_surcharge, na.rm = T))  
            # daily percent of total rides that are (authorized to be) shared OUT of DT Zone
            ) %>% 
   mutate(start_date = as.Date(start_date))


ggplot(shared, aes(x = start_date))+
  geom_line(aes(y = in_dt_zone, color = "Number of Trips in Zone")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = out_dt_zone, color = "Number of Trips OUT of Zone")) +
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("blue", "red")) + 
  scale_y_continuous(labels = comma)+ theme_bw()+
  theme(legend.position="bottom", 
        legend.title = element_blank(), legend.text=element_text(size=8)) +
  scale_x_date(breaks=date_breaks("week")) +
  labs(title =  "Daily Total Number of Trips",
       y = "", x = "") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1))

ggplot(shared, aes(x = start_date))+
  geom_line(aes(y = 100 * pct_sharedOK_in_DT_zone, color = "Percentage of Trips in Zone\nWhich Authorized Shared Ride")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = 100* pct_sharedOK_out_DT_zone, color = "Percentage of Trips OUT of Zone\nWhich Authorized Shared Ride")) +
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("blue", "red")) + 
  scale_y_continuous(labels = comma)+ theme_bw()+
  theme(legend.position="bottom", 
        legend.title = element_blank(), legend.text=element_text(size=8)) +
  scale_x_date(breaks=date_breaks("week")) +
  labs(title =  "Daily Percentage of Trips Authorized Shared Ride",
       y = "%", x = "") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1))

shared_long <- shared %>% 
  select(start_date, pct_sharedOK_in_DT_zone, pct_sharedOK_out_DT_zone) %>% 
  pivot_longer(-start_date, values_to = "pct_sharedOK", names_to = "DTzone")


fit <- lm(pct_sharedOK ~ factor(DTzone), data = shared_long)
shared_long <- drop_na(shared_long) %>% data.frame(fit$residuals)

## F-statistic: 57.05 on 123 and 86 DF,  p-value: < 2.2e-16
shared_zone <- data %>% 
  filter(!is.na(pickup_census_tract), !is.na(dropoff_census_tract)) %>% 
  group_by(pickup_census_tract, dropoff_census_tract, hour=floor_date(start, "hour")) %>% 
  summarise("count_trips" = n(),
            "in_dt_zone" = sum(is_downtown_zone_surcharge, na.rm = T),  
            "out_dt_zone" = sum(!is_downtown_zone_surcharge, na.rm = T),  
            "pct_sharedOK_in_DT_zone" = (sum(is_downtown_zone_surcharge[shared_trip_authorized], na.rm = T) / sum(is_downtown_zone_surcharge, na.rm = T)),
            "pct_sharedOK_out_DT_zone" = (sum(!is_downtown_zone_surcharge[shared_trip_authorized], na.rm = T) / sum(!is_downtown_zone_surcharge, na.rm = T))  
            ) #%>% 


shared_zone_long <- shared_zone %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = c(pct_sharedOK_in_DT_zone, pct_sharedOK_out_DT_zone), 
               values_to = "pct_sharedOK", names_to = "DTzone")
